        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Pur-alpha binds to the motor protein KIF5A, which makes it a possible adapter protein in axo-dendritic transport.\n\n2/10/2017 Pim\n- shRNA KD of Pur alpha (Fig.8) negatively affects Kinesin5-dependent dendritic transport of mRNA granules that contain transcripts for synapse marker proteins such as CAMKII (Fig.1/5/8) and Arc (Fig.1).. Experimental description: Cells: \"We cultured hippocampal neurons from E16 mouse embryos in MEM supplemented with\"" ;
